<font color="#FF0000">REALLY, WHY DO THEY DO THAT?</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jun  6  0:06:48 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Have watched wannabe situations tear several veterans organizations apart in the past 4 years.  It's always painful for everyone involved.  When once mentioning the problem to my mother; she said, &quot;People actually do that?&quot;. She could hardly believe there would be more than isolated cases.  Personally, the mindset is foreign to me.  I wear what I earned, no more.  As a &quot;leg&quot; in the 173rd, I wear the unit patch, but no jump wings.  On top of everything else, there's the IRS, perched like a vulture, ready to revoke a whole organization's tax exemptions if your membership list isn't pure as the driven snow.  
<p><code>-- gerald_ney@icpphil.navy.mil  (Gerald Ney, &quot;professor&quot;, 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


